After migrating to Tomcat 6 (from Tomcat 5), connections made by servlets using URLConnection have additional request headers -> "Cache-Control"and "Pragma".

After looking at the OpenJDK6 implementation of URLConnection class, in 
private void writeRequests() function I have found this lines:
if(!getUseCaches())
{
   requests.setIfNotSet("Cache-Control", "no-cache");
   requests.setIfNotSet("Pragma", "no-cache");
}

Now, urlconnection.getDefaultUseCaches on Tomcat 5 returns null, but on Tomcat 6 the same code returns false, thus Tomcat 6 affects behavior of Java Runtime Environment.
